@ThePoisonedYouth:

Have you tried updating LWJGL (thats the game library Minecraft uses for graphics, sounds and input)? Minecraft never ships with latest version, yet I never run into problem with it and it actually solved few issues for me and my friends in the past.

There is tutorial on Minecraftwiki called "Update LWJGL" with all the info you may need.

@swiftmadness

Just go to the file, right click, open with, choose default programs and make sure that little box is ticked that says "always use the selected program..." and then choose ,java from the list, then click OK.

@JocaDASA

Your running windows 8 and the error says "bad video card drive" just google "windows 8 Minecraft bad video card driver"
